# Wiki Ingest Commands

Add content to the wiki system.

## Manual Ingestion

### Ingest File
```
@ingest <file> [--domain DOMAIN]
```

Processes a markdown or text file and adds it to the wiki.

### Ingest Text
```
@ingest --text "content here" --domain <domain> [--title "Page Title"]
```

Creates a page from raw text content.

## Automatic Ingestion

Drop files in `wiki_system/inbox/` - they'll be auto-processed by the daemon.

Supported formats:
- `.md` - Markdown files
- `.txt` - Plain text files
- Frontmatter supported for metadata

## Domain Routing

Files are automatically routed based on:
1. Explicit `--domain` flag
2. Frontmatter `domain:` field
3. Pattern matching in `config/routing.yaml`
4. Fallback to `general` domain

## Frontmatter Format

```yaml
---
title: Page Title
domain: vulpine-solutions
kind: entity
tags: [python, programming]
summary: Brief description
---
```

## Python API

```python
from pathlib import Path
from llm_wiki.ingest.adapters.markdown import MarkdownAdapter
from llm_wiki.storage.queue import QueueManager

# Using adapter directly
adapter = MarkdownAdapter(wiki_base=Path("wiki_system"))
page = adapter.process_file(Path("notes.md"), domain="homelab")

# Using queue manager
queue = QueueManager(wiki_base=Path("wiki_system"))
queue.enqueue(Path("notes.md"))
```

## CLI Commands

```bash
# Ingest file
uv run llm-wiki ingest file notes.md --domain homelab

# Ingest text
uv run llm-wiki ingest text "My content" --domain personal --title "My Note"

# Check inbox
ls -la wiki_system/inbox/
```

## Processing Pipeline

1. File detected in inbox
2. Source adapter selected (markdown/text)
3. Content extracted (entities, concepts, metadata)
4. Domain routing applied
5. Page stored in domain directory
6. Index updated

## Link Processing

Links in content are converted to wiki format:
- `[text](url)` → `text` (external links removed)
- `[[page-id]]` → preserved as internal links
- Relative links → resolved to page IDs